stylometry: Risksimtable allows you to run multiple simulations at one time.  It allows you to check multiple numbers of inputs to see which one runs most efficiently.  You need to access settings and change the number of simulations to the number of inputs that you want to check.  An example would be when a business is attempting to figure out how to order inventory.  If there are 5 amounts that you need to check, the iterations need to be changed to 5, and then you can run it.  It will find the most efficient number from  those that you listed.
